Dependencies:

Mom -- Mother of all our Python projects. Batteries for Python.
http://pypi.python.org/pypi/mom/0.1.3
https://github.com/gorakhargosh/mom
https://readthedocs.org/projects/mom/

uses for the ASCII85 codec,
see https://mom.readthedocs.org/en/latest/api/codec.html#module-mom.codec

$ sudo pip install mom





compiled dxmain.c after
commander@zombie:~/sources/ghostpdl/gs/psi$ cp ../devices/gdevdsp.h ./
with
commander@zombie:~/sources/ghostpdl/gs/psi$ gcc `pkg-config gtk+-2.0 --cflags` -o meings dxmain.c -lgs `pkg-config gtk+-2.0 --libs`

then linked it to here:
ln -s ~/sources/ghostpdl/gs/psi/meings mgs


this both does soemthing:
(draws the image!)
commander@zombie:~/Projekte/Bücher/friedhofsengel/Tools/Multitone/Code$ ./mgs -dBATCH -dSAFER -sDEVICE=display  ../Recherche/colortransforms.pdf 
(does at least something)
commander@zombie:~/Projekte/Bücher/friedhofsengel/Tools/Multitone/Code$ ./dxmain.py -dBATCH -dSAFER -sDEVICE=display  ../Recherche/colortransforms.pdf 

"-dEPSFitPage" will blow up the eps to fit into the page
"-dEPSCrop" will crop the page to have the size of the eps
